content:
Is anyone interested in working through a proof together for Lean's standard library? I'm working towards the point that I can crank out proofs for proof_wanted theorems but I am not there yet. Pairing together live sounds more fun and productive than asking a sequence of questions on the forums.

I've sketched a proof that an empty hash map always returns none, so we could pair on concretizing that sketch or we could pick a new theorem.
@Timo Carlin-Burns great! I'll DM you
Daniel Windham has marked this topic as resolved.
